name: Palm Sunday
summary: Palm Sunday, marking the beginning of Holy Week, is celebrated by Catholics worldwide to commemorate Jesus' triumphant entry into Jerusalem. Pope Francis skipped his traditional homily during Palm Sunday Mass in St. Peter's Square, an unusual occurrence. Thousands attended Palm Sunday celebrations in Jerusalem despite the ongoing war. Various traditions and customs are observed on Palm Sunday, from the Palm Procession (reminiscent of Jesus' procession) to the use of palm branches (symbolizing victory and triumph). The donkey plays a significant role in the Palm Sunday story, representing humility and peace. Catholics are reminded of several key facts on Palm Sunday, including the importance of Christ's kingship, humility, and belief in His sacrificial death.
